Package: statuser
Type: Package
Title: Stats Functions for Stats Users, Not Statisticians
Version: 0.1.5
Author: Uri Simonsohn [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Uri Simonsohn <urisohn@gmail.com>
Description: Enhanced versions of basic R functions like table2(), t.test2(), and lm2(), 
    produce output designed to be understanded by, and more useful to stats users.
    Default options are informed by best practices (e.g., lm2() uses robust standard errors & 
    flags possible regression problems). Functions like plot_cdf(), plot_density(), and plot_freq() 
    generate in 1 line of code publication-ready descriptive figures most 
    empirical papers should include. Syntax of existing functions is 
    augmented, so if lm(...) works so does lm2(...), but with better defaults, 
    richer and better formatted output, and extra options.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
